For exploited species for which an adequate sample size was obtained (n ≥ 100), a logistic regression model was used to estimate the probability of a fish being landed based on its size. Fish TL was summarized into 5 cm length categories. Proportion of fish considered as landed was calculated for each length category. The model followed the formula: \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
